* {{en}} Jackie Robinson, ''{{lang|en|I Never Had It Made: An Autobiography of Jackie Robinson}}'', New York, Putnam, 1972, rééd. 2003. {{ISBN|0060555971}}. {{Plume}} 
* {{en}} Jules Tygiel, ''{{lang|en|Baseball's Great Experiment: Jackie Robinson and His Legacy}}'', New York, Oxford University Press, 1983, rééd.  2008. 448 p. {{ISBN|0195339282}}. {{Plume}} 
* {{en}} Maury Allen, ''{{lang|en|Jackie Robinson: A Life Remembered}}'', New York, Franklin Watts, 1987. 260 p. {{ISBN|0531150429}}.
* {{en}} David Falkner, ''{{lang|en|Great Time Coming: The Life of Jackie Robinson, from Baseball to Birmingham}}'', New York, Simon & Schuster, 1992. 384 p. {{ISBN|0671793365}}.
* {{en}} Arnold Rampersad, ''{{lang|en|Jackie Robinson, A Biography}}'', New York, Ballantine Books, 1998. 512 p. {{ISBN|034542655X}}. {{Plume}} 
* {{en}} Joseph Dorison (sd), ''{{lang|en|Jackie Robinson: Race, Sports, and the American Dream}}'', Armonk (NY), M.E. Sharpe, 1998, rééd. 2006. 296 p. {{ISBN|0765603179}}.
* {{en}} Jules Tygiel, ''{{lang|en|Extra Bases: Reflections on Jackie Robinson, Race, and Baseball History}}'', Lincoln (NE), University of Nebraska Press, 2002. 165 p. {{ISBN|0803294476}}.  
* {{en}} Scott Simon, ''{{lang|en|Jackie Robinson and the Integration of Baseball}}'', Hoboken (NJ), John Wiley & Sons Inc, 2002. 176 p. {{ISBN|047126153X}}.  
* {{en}} Chris Lamb, ''{{lang|en|Blackout: The Untold Story of Jackie Robinson's First Spring Training}}'', Lincoln (NE), University of Nebraska Press, 2004. {{ISBN|0803229569}}.  
